 # Run router tests\n320: go test ./pkg/router/... -v\n321: \n322: # Run store tests\n323: go test ./pkg/store/... -v\n324: \n325: # Run picod tests\n326: go test ./pkg/picod/... -v\n327: \n328: # Run all pkg tests\n329: go test ./pkg/... -v\n330: \n331: # Run with coverage\n332: go test ./pkg/... -coverprofile=coverage.out -covermode=atomic\n333: \n334: # View coverage report\n335: go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n336: \n337: # Run specific module tests\n338: go test ./pkg/router/jwt_handler_test.go -v\n339: go test ./pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go -v\n340: go test ./pkg/picod/execute_test.go -v\n341: \n342: # Run tests matching pattern\n343: go test ./pkg/... -run \"TestJWT\" -v\n344: go test ./pkg/... -run \"TestStore\" -v\n345: go test ./pkg/... -run \"TestExecute\" -v\n346: ```\n347: \n348: ---\n349: \n350: ## Dependencies\n351: \n352: - Go 1.21+\n353: - `testing` package (stdlib)\n354: - Redis/Valkey for store integration tests (mocked)\n355: - Table-driven test patterns\n356: - Mocking utilities as needed\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ## Acceptance Criteria\n361: \n362: 1. ✅ All test files created (as listed in Test File Status)\n363: 2. ✅ All test scenarios implemented per phase\n364: 3. ✅ Unit test pass rate: 100%\n365: 4. ✅ Test coverage ≥ 70%\n366: 5. ✅ Code passes `go vet` and `gofmt`\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ## Notes\n371: \n372: - Size: L - Large change requiring comprehensive testing across multiple modules\n373: - Tests should use table-driven test patterns for parameterized scenarios\n374: - Use mocked Redis/Valkey clients to avoid external dependencies\n375: - Each task is independently verifiable and can be completed in any order within a phase\n376: - router has most existing tests - focus on missing files and enhancements\n377: - store is completely untested - needs full test suite\n378: - picod has partial coverage - focus on missing files and enhancements\n\n(End of file - total 378 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"previ